    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-08-03T12:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-08-03T12:00:00-05:00" n="1303"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1303">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">860C.01/8–344: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Harriman</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Extract]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-08-03T20:00:00+03:00"
                            >August 3, 1944—8 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received August 4—8:55 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2856. Press for August 2 reported the appointment of Nikolai Aleksandrovich
                        Bulganin<note n="95" xml:id="d1303fn95">Nikolay Alexandrovich Bulganin
                        (Lieutenant General; Colonel General, July 1944; Army General, November
                        1944) acted as a chief political officer on several fronts during the
                        war.</note> as representative of USSR Supreme Soviet to Polish Committee of
                    National Liberation.</p>
                <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Harriman</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
